{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 175°C. Grease a springform tin (Ø 22 cm) with olive oil and dust with polenta.","Sprinkle Demerara sugar and flaked almonds in base of tin. Slice orange thinly and arrange slices in concentric circles on top of almonds. Bake for 5 minutes (175°C) then set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place sugar, Greek yoghurt, olive oil, orange blossom honey and eggs in mixing bowl then beat <nobr>2 min\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add polenta, flour and baking powder then mix <nobr>8 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> ","Transfer batter to prepared tin, ensuring it is evenly spread over orange slices and almonds, then bake for 40-45 minutes (175°C). Meanwhile, clean and dry mixing bowl.","Towards end of baking time, place honey in mixing bowl and warm <nobr>2 min\/80°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Leave cake in tin and, while still warm, make holes all over the surface with a cocktail stick. Spoon over the warm honey, allowing it to sink into the cake. Once completely cool, turn out onto a serving plate and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["olive oil, for greasing","polenta, for dusting","20 g Demerara sugar","10 g flaked almonds","1 blood orange, preferably organic","120 g sugar","140 g Greek yoghurt","100 g olive oil","80 g orange blossom honey","2 medium eggs","100 g polenta","125 g plain flour","1 tsp baking powder","100 g honey"]}],"id":"r175662","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-m_Z7A34me0c\/XZWquooMHrI\/AAAAAAAAfcY\/9fE04_SCXH8MC9Alry0UGJKnl7193Gi8gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_THK_ov3bWY1A2xWk.png","title":"Honey and Blood Orange Cake","publishedAt":"2017-08-28T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"15 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"46 g","calories":"1431 kJ \/ 342 kcal"},"usefulItems":"springform tin (Ø 22 cm), cocktail stick, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This cake can also be made with oranges.","Serve this cake warm with pistachio gelato fo